1
00:01:30,800 --> 00:01:34,520
=Lady Liberty=

2
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:37,980
=Episode 1=

3
00:01:41,180 --> 00:01:42,820
Many readers are very concerned

4
00:01:43,140 --> 00:01:45,940
about whether the two of you
will continue working together.

5
00:01:48,900 --> 00:01:49,380
No.

6
00:01:55,380 --> 00:01:56,660
He Han, you write novels,

7
00:01:56,940 --> 00:01:59,540
and Zhanqiao is your literary editor.

8
00:02:00,220 --> 00:02:01,660
You two are a match made in heaven

9
00:02:01,933 --> 00:02:03,288
in the online fiction industry.

10
00:02:04,460 --> 00:02:05,340
If you had to

11
00:02:05,700 --> 00:02:09,140
use one sentence to evaluate
each other's professional ability,

12
00:02:10,260 --> 00:02:11,050
what would you say?

13
00:02:11,050 --> 00:02:11,740
A genius.

14
00:02:11,940 --> 00:02:12,820
Capable of anything.

15
00:02:13,000 --> 00:02:14,540
Well, why did you stop working together?

16
00:02:14,540 --> 00:02:15,500
Too much pressure.

17
00:02:15,980 --> 00:02:16,660
Too exhausting.

18
00:02:20,140 --> 00:02:20,980
(As far as I know,)

19
00:02:21,940 --> 00:02:24,060
(before, besides
your working relationship,)

20
00:02:24,540 --> 00:02:26,140
(there was also a more)

21
00:02:27,100 --> 00:02:28,220
(intimate one.)

22
00:02:29,111 --> 00:02:31,000
(To put it plainly,
a romantic relationship.)

23
00:02:31,140 --> 00:02:31,777
(Is that true?)

24
00:02:43,540 --> 00:02:44,020
No.

25
00:02:45,140 --> 00:02:45,620
Yes.

26
00:02:45,755 --> 00:02:48,500
Anyway, everything that should happen
between a couple has happened.

27
00:02:48,577 --> 00:02:50,622
We didn't have
a clearly defined relationship.

28
00:02:50,888 --> 00:02:51,740
It's hard to define.

29
00:02:53,180 --> 00:02:54,460
How is that not clearly defined?

30
00:02:54,460 --> 00:02:55,850
How else would you define it?

31
00:02:55,850 --> 00:02:57,300
Being together is being together.

32
00:02:57,533 --> 00:02:59,466
In the end, there was
still a sense of distance.

33
00:03:00,980 --> 00:03:02,620
(And that last bit of distance)

34
00:03:03,600 --> 00:03:04,620
(could not be eliminated.)

35
00:03:08,380 --> 00:03:09,820
(But I made up my mind.)

36
00:03:10,980 --> 00:03:13,940
(Life and work should
both have a new start.)

37
00:03:15,020 --> 00:03:16,060
(Without He Han,)

38
00:03:17,220 --> 00:03:17,980
(I feel)

39
00:03:18,540 --> 00:03:19,820
(I could be better than before.)

40
00:03:20,740 --> 00:03:21,980
I could be healthier

41
00:03:22,420 --> 00:03:23,222
and more relaxed.

42
00:03:24,260 --> 00:03:25,820
Will you go back to how you were before,

43
00:03:25,977 --> 00:03:27,340
reconcile as if nothing happened?

44
00:03:27,540 --> 00:03:27,940
Will you?

45
00:03:28,060 --> 00:03:28,940
Of course.

46
00:03:29,180 --> 00:03:29,580
No.

47
00:03:31,380 --> 00:03:32,300
But I still hope

48
00:03:33,020 --> 00:03:33,940
he can live well.

49
00:03:34,400 --> 00:03:36,300
At the very least,
can you still be friends?

50
00:03:36,500 --> 00:03:37,980
Who wants to be friends with her?

51
00:03:37,980 --> 00:03:39,460
What I lack the least is friends.

52
00:03:39,980 --> 00:03:40,460
Forget it.

53
00:03:41,060 --> 00:03:42,260
For Lin Zhanqiao,

54
00:03:42,460 --> 00:03:44,140
I may not be the best boyfriend,

55
00:03:44,580 --> 00:03:46,420
but I think
I've already done quite well.

56
00:03:47,060 --> 00:03:48,020
I can guarantee

57
00:03:48,820 --> 00:03:49,940
she absolutely won't find

58
00:03:50,020 --> 00:03:51,420
a better author than me.

59
00:03:51,860 --> 00:03:53,644
If you haven't even done your work well,

60
00:03:54,180 --> 00:03:55,380
why look for a boyfriend?

61
00:03:56,600 --> 00:03:58,066
Tame the white horse first,

62
00:03:58,444 --> 00:03:59,510
and then look for a prince.

63
00:04:26,860 --> 00:04:30,740
(Half A Year Ago)

64
00:04:51,900 --> 00:04:52,540
Get up.

65
00:04:53,977 --> 00:04:55,111
Let me sleep a bit more.

66
00:04:55,688 --> 00:04:58,311
Hurry up. We have an appointment
with Mr. Fan at 7:30 AM today.

67
00:04:58,400 --> 00:04:59,066
Get up quickly.

68
00:04:59,460 --> 00:05:01,540
Who schedules a meeting at 7:30 AM?

69
00:05:02,020 --> 00:05:02,740
Hurry up.

70
00:05:03,140 --> 00:05:03,700
Stop sleeping.

71
00:05:03,940 --> 00:05:05,220
He's Mr. Fan, not just anyone.

72
00:05:05,380 --> 00:05:06,300
For him, 7:30 AM

73
00:05:06,300 --> 00:05:07,420
is already noon.

74
00:05:07,740 --> 00:05:09,580
For me, it's not even dawn yet.

75
00:05:09,860 --> 00:05:11,460
You agreed to 7:30 AM.

76
00:05:12,460 --> 00:05:13,820
You agreed on my behalf, okay?

77
00:05:15,060 --> 00:05:17,300
No one would dare make Mr. Fan wait.

78
00:05:17,860 --> 00:05:18,780
Let him wait once.

79
00:05:18,780 --> 00:05:20,260
Everything has a first time.

80
00:05:22,940 --> 00:05:23,940
How about this?

81
00:05:24,540 --> 00:05:25,180
You go first.

82
00:05:25,377 --> 00:05:26,090
After you're done,

83
00:05:26,100 --> 00:05:27,560
you can come back and continue sleeping.

84
00:05:27,580 --> 00:05:28,820
Who could sleep after that?

85
00:05:31,580 --> 00:05:32,940
When you meet him later,

86
00:05:32,940 --> 00:05:33,980
don't keep a straight face.

87
00:05:35,180 --> 00:05:36,340
Be friendlier.

88
00:05:36,340 --> 00:05:37,860
After all, he's from the platform.

89
00:05:39,460 --> 00:05:40,860
Is my attitude that bad?

90
00:05:40,860 --> 00:05:42,020
Isn't it pretty good?

91
00:05:47,260 --> 00:05:48,340
It's all foam.

92
00:05:49,220 --> 00:05:49,620
Hurry up.

93
00:05:52,933 --> 00:05:53,911
Change into this outfit.

94
00:05:53,920 --> 00:05:55,220
No need. I'm already wearing long pants.

95
00:05:55,220 --> 00:05:56,680
That's already showing respect, right?

96
00:05:56,700 --> 00:05:57,540
Just wear this?

97
00:05:57,866 --> 00:05:59,020
Mr. Fan wants to talk to me.

98
00:05:59,020 --> 00:06:00,300
It's not because of my looks,

99
00:06:00,300 --> 00:06:01,060
don't you think?

100
00:06:05,580 --> 00:06:06,060
Wait.

101
00:06:08,666 --> 00:06:09,844
There's a high chance

102
00:06:09,850 --> 00:06:11,120
that Mr. Fan asked you out today

103
00:06:11,120 --> 00:06:12,866
because he's trying
to drive a wedge between us.

104
00:06:12,900 --> 00:06:13,940
He wants to poach you.

105
00:06:14,740 --> 00:06:15,620
So, today, you must

106
00:06:15,620 --> 00:06:16,740
stay firm in your position.

107
00:06:17,300 --> 00:06:18,340
Take his resources,

108
00:06:18,660 --> 00:06:19,740
but don't give him control.

109
00:06:22,060 --> 00:06:23,060
He's not some girl,

110
00:06:23,180 --> 00:06:24,400
so he can't come between us.

111
00:06:38,660 --> 00:06:39,220
Mr. Fan.

112
00:06:41,340 --> 00:06:42,340
The top author.

113
00:06:43,540 --> 00:06:45,330
Sorry to have you come so early.

114
00:06:45,330 --> 00:06:45,820
Not at all.

115
00:06:45,911 --> 00:06:47,740
The morning sets
the tone for the whole day.

116
00:06:47,980 --> 00:06:50,100
I always put the most important matters

117
00:06:50,100 --> 00:06:51,220
in the morning.

118
00:06:51,220 --> 00:06:51,620
Yes.

119
00:06:52,288 --> 00:06:53,622
Let me start with the good news.

120
00:06:53,740 --> 00:06:54,800
Your Shattered Six States

121
00:06:54,860 --> 00:06:57,260
is now popular on our platform.

122
00:06:57,660 --> 00:06:58,340
A coffee, please.

123
00:07:10,300 --> 00:07:11,340
At this rate,

124
00:07:11,340 --> 00:07:13,660
breaking the platform's

125
00:07:13,780 --> 00:07:15,000
reading record since its launch

126
00:07:15,100 --> 00:07:17,140
is not a problem at all.

127
00:07:19,340 --> 00:07:20,820
On behalf of the platform,

128
00:07:20,911 --> 00:07:21,977
on behalf of the...

129
00:07:22,620 --> 00:07:24,340
(Zhanqiao: Where's the face wash?)

130
00:07:26,377 --> 00:07:28,420
On behalf of all the readers
on the platform,

131
00:07:28,580 --> 00:07:30,380
I'd like to thank you, Mr. He Han.

132
00:07:30,380 --> 00:07:31,380
Mr. Fan, you're too kind.

133
00:07:31,380 --> 00:07:33,222
Our relationship
speaks for itself, right?

134
00:07:34,660 --> 00:07:35,780
There's no face wash.

135
00:07:35,780 --> 00:07:37,060
Can't you use the body wash?

136
00:07:40,066 --> 00:07:41,180
Someone's waiting for you?

137
00:07:41,711 --> 00:07:42,820
Then, let's keep this brief.

138
00:07:42,820 --> 00:07:43,180
Sure.

139
00:07:44,540 --> 00:07:45,260
Everyone

140
00:07:45,420 --> 00:07:47,780
is very concerned about your

141
00:07:48,260 --> 00:07:50,260
living situation
and working environment.

142
00:07:50,355 --> 00:07:52,022
So, I made
a special trip to take a look.

143
00:07:52,180 --> 00:07:53,580
The hotel is fine,

144
00:07:54,220 --> 00:07:56,660
but staying here long-term isn't ideal.

145
00:07:57,260 --> 00:07:58,460
The platform is considering

146
00:07:58,460 --> 00:08:01,340
renting a long-term apartment

147
00:08:01,900 --> 00:08:02,820
and arranging

148
00:08:03,260 --> 00:08:04,420
a dedicated cook for you.

149
00:08:04,488 --> 00:08:06,066
Just name whatever you want to eat.

150
00:08:07,020 --> 00:08:08,460
And also a private car and driver,

151
00:08:08,980 --> 00:08:12,300
to take care of your life in every way,

152
00:08:12,660 --> 00:08:13,820
so you can

153
00:08:14,140 --> 00:08:16,980
focus entirely on your writing.

154
00:08:17,100 --> 00:08:18,820
I'm very grateful, Mr. Fan,

155
00:08:19,020 --> 00:08:19,940
but please don't.

156
00:08:20,660 --> 00:08:22,020
I like staying in hotels.

157
00:08:22,500 --> 00:08:24,220
This hotel is just

158
00:08:24,220 --> 00:08:25,860
a temporary place to stay.

159
00:08:26,860 --> 00:08:28,140
Isn't everywhere like that?

160
00:08:29,100 --> 00:08:29,740
You see,

161
00:08:31,060 --> 00:08:32,660
talking with a writer

162
00:08:33,180 --> 00:08:34,500
is always so insightful.

163
00:08:36,220 --> 00:08:37,540
Sir, your coffee.

164
00:08:51,200 --> 00:08:52,540
(7:50 AM, Zhanqiao:
I'm going home for a bit. Talk later.)

165
00:08:54,500 --> 00:08:57,300
To better serve you,

166
00:08:58,340 --> 00:08:59,340
I have an idea.

167
00:09:00,000 --> 00:09:01,860
Let me know
if you think it's appropriate.

168
00:09:01,940 --> 00:09:02,340
Please.

169
00:09:04,980 --> 00:09:06,740
As for Lin Zhanqiao's company,

170
00:09:08,340 --> 00:09:09,340
we at Dingqi

171
00:09:10,060 --> 00:09:11,180
can consider taking a stake,

172
00:09:11,620 --> 00:09:13,380
investing to support your growth.

173
00:09:16,700 --> 00:09:18,660
So we've finally gotten
to the point, Mr. Fan.

174
00:09:19,780 --> 00:09:20,860
But unfortunately, there are

175
00:09:20,911 --> 00:09:22,620
three shareholders
in Lin Zhanqiao's company,

176
00:09:22,640 --> 00:09:23,644
and I'm not one of them.

177
00:09:23,740 --> 00:09:25,660
But you're the company's top author.

178
00:09:25,660 --> 00:09:26,980
You can influence them.

179
00:09:28,500 --> 00:09:28,980
Besides,

180
00:09:29,700 --> 00:09:31,100
I can fully fund it

181
00:09:32,180 --> 00:09:33,900
and set up a studio

182
00:09:34,060 --> 00:09:35,460
just for you, Mr. He Han.

183
00:09:37,540 --> 00:09:39,700
Your market value is different now.

184
00:09:39,900 --> 00:09:40,900
I can meet

185
00:09:41,020 --> 00:09:42,540
any request you have.

186
00:09:42,540 --> 00:09:43,980
Impressive, Mr. Fan.

187
00:09:55,060 --> 00:09:55,620
Mr. Fan,

188
00:09:57,060 --> 00:09:58,355
do you know how much I've earned

189
00:09:58,377 --> 00:10:00,250
from Shattered Six States
since it launched?

190
00:10:00,250 --> 00:10:02,940
Do you know how much I take
and how much Lin Zhanqiao takes?

191
00:10:03,580 --> 00:10:05,620
I don't know how you split it.

192
00:10:06,460 --> 00:10:08,500
The share between each editor and author

193
00:10:09,420 --> 00:10:11,620
can vary a lot.

194
00:10:11,780 --> 00:10:12,260
That's true.

195
00:10:13,500 --> 00:10:15,500
The company takes one-third first,

196
00:10:15,900 --> 00:10:16,700
Lin Zhanqiao and I

197
00:10:17,060 --> 00:10:19,220
split what's left evenly.

198
00:10:22,900 --> 00:10:24,060
Then, Mr. He Han,

199
00:10:24,460 --> 00:10:25,820
you're quite generous.

200
00:10:26,300 --> 00:10:27,300
It's not generosity.

201
00:10:28,060 --> 00:10:29,220
It's what she deserves.

202
00:10:33,180 --> 00:10:34,860
So, you mean

203
00:10:35,380 --> 00:10:36,940
you intend to stay tied

204
00:10:37,380 --> 00:10:38,540
to Lin Zhanqiao long term?

205
00:10:38,780 --> 00:10:40,820
Unless there's some special reason,

206
00:10:41,220 --> 00:10:42,060
that's right.

207
00:11:39,220 --> 00:11:39,980
What are you doing?

208
00:11:40,780 --> 00:11:42,340
Replying to emails. What's up?

209
00:11:43,580 --> 00:11:44,660
I didn't go home last night.

210
00:11:45,111 --> 00:11:46,260
(Proposal Revision Suggestions)

211
00:11:46,260 --> 00:11:46,820
So?

212
00:11:47,940 --> 00:11:50,380
No matter how late it was,
I would always go back.

213
00:11:50,980 --> 00:11:51,740
But last night,

214
00:11:51,740 --> 00:11:54,022
He Han said
since it was raining, I shouldn't leave.

215
00:11:54,060 --> 00:11:55,020
So, I stayed.

216
00:11:55,380 --> 00:11:57,460
So, you didn't sleep well
and came back to catch up?

217
00:11:57,780 --> 00:11:59,780
No, I slept quite well.

218
00:12:00,780 --> 00:12:02,460
But when I woke up, I realized

219
00:12:02,480 --> 00:12:03,990
there was no toothbrush or toothpaste,

220
00:12:04,100 --> 00:12:05,060
so I came back.

221
00:12:05,660 --> 00:12:06,820
Isn't that a good thing?

222
00:12:07,180 --> 00:12:07,900
If there were any,

223
00:12:07,900 --> 00:12:09,340
they'd be left by another woman.

224
00:12:10,260 --> 00:12:12,380
That's not what I meant.

225
00:12:12,580 --> 00:12:13,980
What I mean is,

226
00:12:14,220 --> 00:12:16,420
should I bring some things over?

227
00:12:16,666 --> 00:12:18,244
Otherwise, next time I stay there,

228
00:12:18,250 --> 00:12:20,580
there'll still be nothing,
and I'll have to come back again.

229
00:12:20,580 --> 00:12:22,400
That's so inconvenient, don't you think?

230
00:12:23,300 --> 00:12:24,220
What did He Han say?

231
00:12:26,460 --> 00:12:27,500
Do I need to ask him?

232
00:12:27,700 --> 00:12:29,860
It's not like I'd call him

233
00:12:29,940 --> 00:12:31,180
just to ask if I can bring

234
00:12:31,180 --> 00:12:32,540
a toothbrush and toothpaste.

235
00:12:33,700 --> 00:12:35,020
He should have asked you first.

236
00:12:35,422 --> 00:12:37,600
Otherwise, it means
he doesn't want you staying over.

237
00:12:40,180 --> 00:12:40,980
You know what?

238
00:12:42,260 --> 00:12:43,500
Last night,

239
00:12:43,580 --> 00:12:45,940
he was the one who asked me to stay.

240
00:12:46,220 --> 00:12:47,900
Of course, he had asked before too,

241
00:12:47,900 --> 00:12:49,260
but I never agreed.

242
00:12:49,500 --> 00:12:51,940
Because I think leaving at night
and leaving in the morning

243
00:12:52,340 --> 00:12:53,740
are different.

244
00:12:53,940 --> 00:12:54,980
Leaving at night means

245
00:12:54,980 --> 00:12:56,420
you're still dating,

246
00:12:56,500 --> 00:12:58,420
but living separate lives.

247
00:12:58,533 --> 00:12:59,711
But leaving in the morning

248
00:12:59,740 --> 00:13:01,260
means you've accepted

249
00:13:01,260 --> 00:13:02,644
that you're going to live together.

250
00:13:05,580 --> 00:13:06,020
Hey,

251
00:13:06,380 --> 00:13:07,740
are you even listening to me?

252
00:13:09,660 --> 00:13:11,460
Then, just bring
a toothbrush and toothpaste

253
00:13:11,460 --> 00:13:12,420
and go try it out first.

254
00:13:14,500 --> 00:13:15,620
What about the pillow?

255
00:13:16,020 --> 00:13:16,980
Forget the pillow.

256
00:13:32,980 --> 00:13:33,540
You're back.

257
00:13:34,620 --> 00:13:35,460
That was fast.

258
00:13:36,466 --> 00:13:38,700
The hotel slippers were too big
that I almost tripped.

259
00:13:39,100 --> 00:13:40,820
How did it go with Mr. Fan today?

260
00:13:41,740 --> 00:13:42,740
It was alright.

261
00:13:43,500 --> 00:13:44,420
Just like you said,

262
00:13:44,580 --> 00:13:46,466
he was trying
to drive a wedge between us.

263
00:13:46,980 --> 00:13:48,220
But I stayed firm

264
00:13:48,300 --> 00:13:49,340
and still kept it polite.

265
00:13:49,500 --> 00:13:50,060
You know,

266
00:13:50,300 --> 00:13:51,500
I did really well.

267
00:13:52,300 --> 00:13:53,780
What kind of riches did he offer you?

268
00:13:59,380 --> 00:14:00,700
Half the kingdom!

269
00:14:02,620 --> 00:14:04,020
Then, how did you shut him down?

270
00:14:06,380 --> 00:14:07,220
I told him

271
00:14:09,860 --> 00:14:11,700
I'd choose the beauty over the kingdom.

272
00:14:13,620 --> 00:14:14,220
Start writing.

273
00:14:14,311 --> 00:14:16,000
I'm here to remind you
to submit your draft.

274
00:14:16,020 --> 00:14:17,420
Beauty and the draft, both handled.

275
00:14:17,620 --> 00:14:18,500
Start writing.

276
00:14:18,555 --> 00:14:19,980
What's wrong with you? Start writing.

277
00:14:20,088 --> 00:14:21,500
Or you'll run out of time later.

278
00:14:21,500 --> 00:14:22,900
Relax, there's plenty of time to write.

279
00:14:22,900 --> 00:14:24,133
Just start writing, okay?

280
00:14:26,380 --> 00:14:26,980
Your pillow?

281
00:14:28,300 --> 00:14:29,940
The hotel pillow isn't very comfortable.

282
00:14:30,777 --> 00:14:32,244
Then, what do you sleep on at home?

283
00:14:32,380 --> 00:14:33,380
I ordered a new one.

284
00:14:33,711 --> 00:14:34,620
It'll arrive tomorrow.

285
00:14:35,460 --> 00:14:36,820
So you're leaving this here, right?

286
00:14:38,540 --> 00:14:38,980
Can't I?

287
00:14:40,333 --> 00:14:41,380
It's not that you can't.

288
00:14:42,220 --> 00:14:43,577
If you think it's not appropriate,

289
00:14:43,740 --> 00:14:44,730
I can take it away.

290
00:14:44,730 --> 00:14:46,140
No need. It's fine to leave it here.

291
00:14:47,420 --> 00:14:49,133
I'm not planning to stay here every day.

292
00:14:49,660 --> 00:14:51,100
But if I stay occasionally,

293
00:14:51,500 --> 00:14:53,100
without these daily items,

294
00:14:53,120 --> 00:14:54,440
it'll be very inconvenient for me.

295
00:14:54,460 --> 00:14:55,420
Yes, of course.

296
00:14:55,820 --> 00:14:56,260
Got it.

297
00:15:01,820 --> 00:15:02,460
It's fine.

298
00:15:02,900 --> 00:15:03,460
It's good.

299
00:15:18,220 --> 00:15:19,100
Alright.

300
00:15:19,460 --> 00:15:20,420
Start writing.

301
00:15:21,340 --> 00:15:22,700
Start writing. Alright.

302
00:15:22,700 --> 00:15:23,460
Start writing...

303
00:15:23,460 --> 00:15:24,260
I don't want.

304
00:15:24,260 --> 00:15:25,220
Start writing.

305
00:15:25,300 --> 00:15:27,780
It's still early.
There's plenty of time.

306
00:15:27,980 --> 00:15:29,940
You'll run out of time again
and get rushed.

307
00:15:30,266 --> 00:15:31,580
Okay, I won't bother you. Go write.

308
00:15:31,580 --> 00:15:32,800
Call me when you're done.

309
00:15:41,020 --> 00:15:41,660
Don't worry.

310
00:15:42,088 --> 00:15:43,700
I won't take up too much of your space.

311
00:15:43,700 --> 00:15:44,820
Just some sleepwear

312
00:15:44,820 --> 00:15:46,340
and those daily items,

313
00:15:46,340 --> 00:15:46,900
you know.

314
00:16:11,660 --> 00:16:12,700
The back...

315
00:16:35,100 --> 00:16:35,860
Where did you go?

316
00:16:36,660 --> 00:16:38,020
I went downstairs for a coffee.

317
00:16:38,066 --> 00:16:39,020
Drinking while writing.

318
00:16:39,220 --> 00:16:40,355
I'll head back up in a bit.

319
00:17:16,660 --> 00:17:17,700
Which cafe?

320
00:17:18,660 --> 00:17:19,660
I was just at Starbucks.

321
00:17:19,980 --> 00:17:20,780
What a coincidence.

322
00:17:20,822 --> 00:17:22,340
A classmate
I haven't seen in a long time

323
00:17:22,340 --> 00:17:23,370
suddenly came to Shanghai to see me.

324
00:17:23,370 --> 00:17:24,420
I'm going to meet him now.

325
00:17:26,311 --> 00:17:27,600
When will you come back?

326
00:17:27,866 --> 00:17:30,100
If we eat,
it'll probably be after dinner.

327
00:17:30,177 --> 00:17:31,800
Remember to submit your draft today.

328
00:17:31,900 --> 00:17:33,688
I know. I'll write
whenever I get the chance.

329
00:17:33,940 --> 00:17:34,580
I'll finish it.

330
00:17:35,460 --> 00:17:35,860
Bye.

331
00:18:06,777 --> 00:18:07,577
Morning, Ms. Lin.

332
00:18:24,200 --> 00:18:24,940
Morning, Ms. Lin.

333
00:18:25,300 --> 00:18:25,660
Morning.

334
00:18:26,977 --> 00:18:27,733
Morning, Ms. Lin.

335
00:18:27,866 --> 00:18:28,300
Morning.

336
00:18:28,300 --> 00:18:30,170
Keep an eye on the authors
who need to submit today.

337
00:18:30,180 --> 00:18:30,770
Morning, Ms. Lin.

338
00:18:30,780 --> 00:18:31,100
Morning.

339
00:18:31,300 --> 00:18:31,980
Morning, Ms. Lin.

340
00:18:32,060 --> 00:18:32,733
Alright, Ms. Zhao.

341
00:18:32,780 --> 00:18:33,850
Get it to me before the end of the day.

342
00:18:33,860 --> 00:18:34,850
- Morning, Ms. Lin.
- Morning, Ms. Lin.

343
00:18:34,860 --> 00:18:35,220
Morning.

344
00:18:36,100 --> 00:18:37,220
Why are you so happy today?

345
00:18:37,220 --> 00:18:38,140
What's the good news?

346
00:18:38,340 --> 00:18:38,780
Me?

347
00:18:39,180 --> 00:18:39,740
Am I?

348
00:18:41,066 --> 00:18:42,900
He Han's momentum
has been strong lately.

349
00:18:43,200 --> 00:18:45,066
Hong Qigong has also
been making steady progress.

350
00:18:45,980 --> 00:18:47,020
I'm indeed in a good mood.

351
00:18:47,660 --> 00:18:48,620
Aren't you the same,

352
00:18:49,020 --> 00:18:49,460
Ms. Zhao?

353
00:18:49,480 --> 00:18:50,600
Let me run something by you.

354
00:18:50,620 --> 00:18:52,330
At the proposal meeting later,
I'll go first, then you.

355
00:18:52,340 --> 00:18:52,933
How about it?

356
00:18:53,022 --> 00:18:53,955
Got something going on?

357
00:18:54,133 --> 00:18:55,490
I'm meeting Ling Yikai for lunch.

358
00:18:55,490 --> 00:18:56,410
I need to go early,

359
00:18:56,410 --> 00:18:57,355
or there'll be a line.

360
00:18:57,380 --> 00:18:58,850
And you still dare to go eat with him?

361
00:18:59,140 --> 00:19:00,940
Last time at Auntie Noodles,
it was 58 yuan,

362
00:19:01,300 --> 00:19:02,930
and he kept trying to get you to pay.

363
00:19:02,930 --> 00:19:03,860
Not every woman

364
00:19:03,860 --> 00:19:05,580
