anything truly good yet.

484
00:24:53,020 --> 00:24:53,900
Excuse me.

485
00:24:53,977 --> 00:24:55,100
Your dishes are all served.

486
00:24:55,100 --> 00:24:56,377
Please settle the bill first.

487
00:24:58,780 --> 00:25:00,111
One hundred twenty-eight yuan.

488
00:25:03,060 --> 00:25:03,500
I'll pay.

489
00:25:09,540 --> 00:25:09,900
Alright.

490
00:25:13,540 --> 00:25:15,260
Do you never treat women to meals?

491
00:25:16,100 --> 00:25:16,540
Not really.

492
00:25:21,580 --> 00:25:22,900
I often treat men.

493
00:25:26,580 --> 00:25:27,900
Right, you'll still need

494
00:25:27,900 --> 00:25:29,020
to follow up with them later.

495
00:25:29,180 --> 00:25:29,570
Alright.

496
00:25:29,570 --> 00:25:30,260
Okay, no problem.

497
00:25:30,260 --> 00:25:31,270
That's about it for today.

498
00:25:31,380 --> 00:25:31,780
Okay.

499
00:25:32,133 --> 00:25:33,644
Let's leave it at that for lunch.

500
00:25:33,755 --> 00:25:35,466
Alright, let's wrap up the meeting.

501
00:25:37,180 --> 00:25:37,780
Hi, Ms. Mei.

502
00:25:41,420 --> 00:25:43,500
- Ms. Mei, you look beautiful today.
- Hi, Ms. Mei.

503
00:25:48,177 --> 00:25:50,220
Dressed like that
and holding a takeaway box,

504
00:25:50,577 --> 00:25:51,911
doesn't it look a bit odd?

505
00:25:52,000 --> 00:25:54,288
There's a business event
at the company this afternoon.

506
00:25:54,511 --> 00:25:56,311
Did everything go smoothly
after you moved in?

507
00:25:57,340 --> 00:25:58,380
Didn't he act cute

508
00:25:58,380 --> 00:26:00,210
and ask you to go back
at noon to eat with him?

509
00:26:01,220 --> 00:26:03,540
He has to meet
a high school classmate at noon today,

510
00:26:03,977 --> 00:26:05,220
and won't be back until evening.

511
00:26:05,260 --> 00:26:06,800
First day of officially living together,

512
00:26:06,800 --> 00:26:08,400
and he's already going out
with someone else?

513
00:26:08,420 --> 00:26:09,970
We've already known each other so well.

514
00:26:10,100 --> 00:26:11,622
A day or two doesn't make a difference.

515
00:26:12,980 --> 00:26:13,780
But you know,

516
00:26:14,180 --> 00:26:15,420
it still feels a bit strange.

517
00:26:16,100 --> 00:26:17,460
I've been in and out

518
00:26:17,460 --> 00:26:19,060
of that suite many times before.

519
00:26:19,500 --> 00:26:20,300
But I always felt

520
00:26:20,380 --> 00:26:21,540
it was He Han's place.

521
00:26:22,111 --> 00:26:23,911
But after staying
just one night yesterday,

522
00:26:24,180 --> 00:26:25,060
I switched to my own

523
00:26:25,060 --> 00:26:26,420
pillow, slippers, and toothbrush.

524
00:26:27,300 --> 00:26:28,940
At least now it feels like

525
00:26:29,460 --> 00:26:31,020
part of that space belongs to me.

526
00:26:31,666 --> 00:26:33,488
So you still brought your pillow over.

527
00:26:34,740 --> 00:26:35,940
If I'm going to move in anyway,

528
00:26:36,044 --> 00:26:37,190
might as well go all the way.

529
00:26:37,260 --> 00:26:39,000
What's with just
a toothbrush and toothpaste?

530
00:26:39,020 --> 00:26:40,380
It's not like I have nowhere to live

531
00:26:40,380 --> 00:26:41,533
and I have to stay with him.

532
00:26:41,860 --> 00:26:42,740
If he doesn't want it,

533
00:26:42,940 --> 00:26:43,820
he can just tell me.

534
00:26:44,100 --> 00:26:44,620
I'll leave.

535
00:26:44,780 --> 00:26:45,777
If he doesn't want it,

536
00:26:45,780 --> 00:26:47,933
you can just walk away
with your toothbrush and toothpaste,

537
00:26:47,955 --> 00:26:48,555
no big deal.

538
00:26:48,733 --> 00:26:51,088
But with pillows and slippers,
how are you going to carry all that?

539
00:26:51,088 --> 00:26:52,777
He didn't say he didn't want it.

540
00:26:52,940 --> 00:26:53,977
Well, did he say he did?

541
00:27:30,420 --> 00:27:31,980
What does Li Weifeng's wife do?

542
00:27:32,666 --> 00:27:34,060
She's so precise and ruthless.

543
00:27:34,866 --> 00:27:36,700
Can those chat records
she deleted that day

544
00:27:36,980 --> 00:27:37,780
be recovered?

545
00:27:38,740 --> 00:27:39,260
No.

546
00:27:39,977 --> 00:27:41,980
Then, how are you
going to prove you're innocent?

547
00:27:42,140 --> 00:27:42,940
I won't.

548
00:27:43,044 --> 00:27:44,666
If she wants me to look guilty,

549
00:27:44,733 --> 00:27:45,977
I'll show her guilty.

550
00:27:46,220 --> 00:27:47,140
In a few days,

551
00:27:47,244 --> 00:27:48,644
she'll wish I were innocent.

552
00:27:49,180 --> 00:27:51,220
Better to break ten bridges
than ruin one marriage.

553
00:27:51,700 --> 00:27:52,620
I'm warning you.

554
00:27:52,711 --> 00:27:53,930
If she doesn't get a wake-up call,

555
00:27:53,940 --> 00:27:55,866
she won't realize
how many issues she has.

556
00:27:57,460 --> 00:27:59,260
Ms. Lin, Mr. He Han's
update has come in.

557
00:28:15,740 --> 00:28:16,260
That's rare.

558
00:28:17,340 --> 00:28:18,422
He went out having fun,

559
00:28:18,488 --> 00:28:20,222
and he still finished his daily update.

560
00:28:21,111 --> 00:28:22,620
What is he doing with his classmate?

561
00:28:29,540 --> 00:28:30,700
I'll have a roast goose,

562
00:28:31,300 --> 00:28:32,140
one choy sum,

563
00:28:32,900 --> 00:28:34,580
and a beef chow fun.

564
00:28:36,180 --> 00:28:37,220
And a whisky, please.

565
00:28:38,180 --> 00:28:39,260
Macallan 18.

566
00:28:39,820 --> 00:28:40,420
Single cask.

567
00:28:41,355 --> 00:28:42,140
Alright, thank you.

568
00:29:02,500 --> 00:29:03,020
Hello.

569
00:29:17,111 --> 00:29:19,311
I'm going out for dinner
with a classmate tonight,

570
00:29:19,340 --> 00:29:20,711
and I might go for a drink after.

571
00:29:20,755 --> 00:29:21,940
Don't wait for me.

572
00:29:22,511 --> 00:29:23,460
Drink less, alright?

573
00:29:24,300 --> 00:29:25,380
Don't worry. Bye.

574
00:29:26,200 --> 00:29:27,780
The Macallan 18 is a single cask, right?

575
00:29:27,860 --> 00:29:28,500
Yes, sir.

576
00:29:54,780 --> 00:29:55,460
My classmate.

577
00:30:01,980 --> 00:30:02,780
I mean,

578
00:30:02,780 --> 00:30:04,180
wasn't it better before?

579
00:30:04,540 --> 00:30:05,933
We worked and ate together.

580
00:30:06,000 --> 00:30:07,300
Just the two of us, happy,

581
00:30:07,300 --> 00:30:08,140
without any pressure.

582
00:30:08,150 --> 00:30:09,311
Now you want it to become

583
00:30:09,333 --> 00:30:11,180
the two of us working
together 24 hours a day,

584
00:30:11,180 --> 00:30:12,100
living together.

585
00:30:12,177 --> 00:30:13,880
If this goes on,
we will get tired of it.

586
00:30:14,020 --> 00:30:15,380
I'm not sick of you.

587
00:30:16,180 --> 00:30:17,340
So you're sick of me?

588
00:30:17,540 --> 00:30:18,370
No.

589
00:30:18,370 --> 00:30:19,500
Anyone would get tired.

590
00:30:19,500 --> 00:30:20,140
Think about it.

591
00:30:20,150 --> 00:30:21,844
It's not just my work
you want to manage,

592
00:30:21,850 --> 00:30:23,100
and you want to manage my life too?

593
00:30:23,100 --> 00:30:24,220
I'm not managing your life.

594
00:30:24,220 --> 00:30:25,700
You were the one who kept me last night.

595
00:30:25,700 --> 00:30:27,540
Yes, because it was pouring last night.

596
00:30:27,711 --> 00:30:29,780
But before, when it rained,
I also asked you to stay.

597
00:30:29,860 --> 00:30:31,060
Before, I never stayed.

598
00:30:31,733 --> 00:30:34,555
Leaving in the morning and leaving
at night are completely different.

599
00:30:34,740 --> 00:30:36,100
The reason I stayed last night

600
00:30:36,300 --> 00:30:37,980
was that I accepted
that our relationship

601
00:30:37,980 --> 00:30:39,300
could move a step further.

602
00:30:39,460 --> 00:30:40,250
I'm ready.

603
00:30:40,250 --> 00:30:42,100
I can treat this place as my home.

604
00:30:42,100 --> 00:30:43,220
How would I know?

605
00:30:43,660 --> 00:30:45,060
How would I know you're ready?

606
00:30:45,260 --> 00:30:46,860
Did you ever ask me if I was ready?

607
00:30:46,977 --> 00:30:48,140
You made the decision yourself

608
00:30:48,140 --> 00:30:49,220
and forced me to accept the result.

609
00:30:49,220 --> 00:30:50,460
And I can't have any say in it?

610
00:30:50,460 --> 00:30:52,020
You can. Go ahead.

611
00:30:52,020 --> 00:30:53,500
My opinion is that before
you make a decision,

612
00:30:53,500 --> 00:30:55,377
you should discuss it
with me first, alright?

613
00:30:56,422 --> 00:30:57,260
It's not just this once.

614
00:30:57,260 --> 00:30:59,555
Hasn't it always been
like this before, Lin Zhanqiao?

615
00:31:00,060 --> 00:31:01,980
The world doesn't revolve around you.

616
00:31:02,088 --> 00:31:03,460
Your pace isn't the only correct one.

617
00:31:03,460 --> 00:31:05,180
Just because others can't keep up
with you doesn't mean they're wrong!

618
00:31:05,260 --> 00:31:06,540
You don't have any pace at all.

619
00:31:06,540 --> 00:31:09,020
Every time you run
into a problem, you avoid it!

620
00:31:09,020 --> 00:31:10,180
You always say "avoid!"

621
00:31:10,780 --> 00:31:12,900
Is this avoiding?
I'm looking at the bigger picture.

622
00:31:13,022 --> 00:31:14,900
I care about you.
I don't want to hurt you.

623
00:31:15,140 --> 00:31:16,020
That's why I did it.

624
00:31:16,140 --> 00:31:17,220
So what do you plan to do?

625
00:31:17,220 --> 00:31:18,140
I don't know!

626
00:31:18,460 --> 00:31:19,500
I'm not ready!

627
00:31:19,755 --> 00:31:21,780
I never thought
you'd treat this place as home!

628
00:31:22,580 --> 00:31:23,980
I don't even treat this as home!

629
00:31:24,100 --> 00:31:25,700
It's just a hotel suite!

630
00:31:30,380 --> 00:31:32,060
Why can't you wait for me?

631
00:31:32,500 --> 00:31:33,420
Wait until I find

632
00:31:33,420 --> 00:31:35,088
a place suitable
for us to live together.

633
00:31:35,111 --> 00:31:35,860
Wait for you...

634
00:31:35,860 --> 00:31:36,980
You always say wait for you!

635
00:31:36,980 --> 00:31:37,820
Wait until when?

636
00:31:37,980 --> 00:31:40,400
When did you even start looking?
Have you even started now?

637
00:31:40,580 --> 00:31:42,060
Fine, you say you're not ready!

638
00:31:42,060 --> 00:31:44,060
Then, can't I also say
you either get ready now,

639
00:31:44,060 --> 00:31:45,180
or never have to get ready at all?

640
00:31:45,180 --> 00:31:46,380
Don't get ready, then!

641
00:32:16,140 --> 00:32:16,660
He Han,

642
00:32:17,980 --> 00:32:19,420
this is the last time I'm here.

643
00:32:19,420 --> 00:32:20,780
I won't come back again.

644
00:32:21,060 --> 00:32:22,820
I never forced you to marry me.

645
00:32:22,820 --> 00:32:24,980
It's not that I
value marriage that much!

646
00:32:26,660 --> 00:32:27,380
I just don't want

647
00:32:27,380 --> 00:32:29,700
to keep getting dragged into
this endless push and pull!

648
00:32:29,700 --> 00:32:30,940
I've had enough! I'm tired!

649
00:32:30,940 --> 00:32:32,220
I just want an answer.

650
00:32:32,888 --> 00:32:34,700
Whether it's good or bad,
together or apart,

651
00:32:34,700 --> 00:32:35,620
I can accept it.

652
00:32:35,740 --> 00:32:36,820
But what I can't accept

653
00:32:37,700 --> 00:32:38,620
is this ambiguity.

654
00:32:41,140 --> 00:32:47,140
(The Day Before)

655
00:32:51,540 --> 00:32:52,355
Can't get a ride?

656
00:32:54,555 --> 00:32:55,866
The rain is too heavy.

657
00:32:57,260 --> 00:32:58,900
The current queue number

658
00:32:59,420 --> 00:33:00,460
is 82.

659
00:33:02,111 --> 00:33:03,500
Then, wait until the rain stops.

660
00:33:03,733 --> 00:33:06,355
But the forecast says it won't stop
until tomorrow morning.

661
00:33:15,300 --> 00:33:16,420
Then, leave tomorrow.

662
00:33:18,500 --> 00:33:21,060
♪I keep asking myself♪

663
00:33:22,940 --> 00:33:26,420
♪What it is I should become♪

664
00:33:28,100 --> 00:33:31,940
♪To follow what my heart truly wants♪

665
00:33:31,940 --> 00:33:33,020
(Because of a toothbrush)

666
00:33:34,620 --> 00:33:35,420
(and a pillow,)

667
00:33:37,500 --> 00:33:38,340
(after that day,)

668
00:33:39,620 --> 00:33:40,860
(He Han and I broke up.)

669
00:33:42,420 --> 00:33:44,020
(Or rather, we completely fell apart.)

670
00:33:46,780 --> 00:33:49,860
♪Like a drifting dandelion♪

671
00:33:53,260 --> 00:33:53,900
(In my world,)

672
00:33:53,900 --> 00:33:56,111
(there is no longer a place
for someone named He Han.)

673
00:33:57,933 --> 00:33:59,540
(With so many people in this world,)

674
00:34:01,380 --> 00:34:03,500
(I will find someone willing)

675
00:34:05,100 --> 00:34:06,220
(to face storms with me.)

676
00:34:06,220 --> 00:34:09,570
♪In a flower shop at the corner♪

677
00:34:10,000 --> 00:34:15,970
♪Even spring borrows its fragrance♪

678
00:34:17,020 --> 00:34:23,500
♪Moonlight keeps me company
on lonely roads♪

679
00:34:24,180 --> 00:34:30,910
♪Across fields of blooms,
a boat awaits me♪

680
00:34:31,420 --> 00:34:38,180
♪Swaying in the shape of the wind♪

681
00:34:38,660 --> 00:34:43,460
♪Not waiting for calm to come♪

682
00:34:46,140 --> 00:34:49,200
♪I want to go on like this♪

683
00:34:50,820 --> 00:34:54,240
♪Moving forward, not alone♪

684
00:34:54,820 --> 00:35:01,190
♪This moment
is worth more than anything♪

685
00:35:01,520 --> 00:35:03,550
♪No need to define the distance♪

686
00:35:03,580 --> 00:35:08,460
♪Let trials become my scenery♪

687
00:35:09,220 --> 00:35:14,900
♪A life not yet full begins again♪

688
00:35:29,466 --> 00:35:31,466
Why are you putting
the toothbrush on display?

689
00:35:33,460 --> 00:35:34,220
A pillar of shame.

690
00:35:35,740 --> 00:35:36,820
It's a constant reminder

691
00:35:37,060 --> 00:35:38,020
of how stupid I was

692
00:35:38,311 --> 00:35:39,755
and how I lost all dignity.

693
00:35:40,700 --> 00:35:41,460
The same mistake

694
00:35:42,300 --> 00:35:44,020
should only be made once in a lifetime.

695
00:35:50,380 --> 00:35:51,660
There's no room to negotiate?

696
00:35:58,380 --> 00:35:59,980
Is it because he has other girls there,

697
00:36:00,466 --> 00:36:02,180
so he asked you to bring your toothbrush

698
00:36:02,180 --> 00:36:04,866
and pillow back so that you don't get
in the way of him seeing other women?

699
00:36:06,820 --> 00:36:07,300
No.

700
00:36:13,222 --> 00:36:15,555
Are you still working together
on Shattered Six States?

701
00:36:22,866 --> 00:36:25,244
For Shattered Six States,
I will find you another editor.

702
00:36:25,933 --> 00:36:28,222
I don't want to have
anything to do with you anymore.

703
00:36:28,300 --> 00:36:30,659
From now on, you stay in your hotel,
and I'll go back to my home.

704
00:36:30,660 --> 00:36:32,500
You write your novels,
and I'll do my editing.

705
00:36:33,060 --> 00:36:33,660
Lin Zhanqiao,

706
00:36:35,180 --> 00:36:36,780
are you turning our relationship problem

707
00:36:36,780 --> 00:36:38,220
into a work issue?

708
00:36:42,300 --> 00:36:42,780
Fine.

709
00:36:44,777 --> 00:36:46,100
But where are you going to find

710
00:36:46,100 --> 00:36:47,140
another author like me?

711
00:36:47,420 --> 00:36:48,820
I can find plenty anywhere.

712
00:36:50,422 --> 00:36:52,610
Someone who's younger than you,
more disciplined than you,

713
00:36:52,622 --> 00:36:54,155
better at writing than you, and...

714
00:36:54,688 --> 00:36:56,380
who knows how to respect their editor.

715
00:36:56,410 --> 00:36:57,660
You don't need to find plenty.

716
00:36:57,660 --> 00:36:59,020
If you find even one, I lose.

717
00:36:59,777 --> 00:37:00,820
Then, you've already lost.

718
00:37:01,700 --> 00:37:02,340
We'll see.

719
00:37:22,511 --> 00:37:24,540
My company doesn't only
have him as an author.

720
00:37:29,022 --> 00:37:31,340
I really didn't expect
you two to break up so suddenly.

721
00:37:32,340 --> 00:37:33,620
He Han is now

722
00:37:33,620 --> 00:37:34,700
our biggest asset.

723
00:37:34,940 --> 00:37:36,300
We don't want to lose this asset

724
00:37:36,300 --> 00:37:37,100
for any reason.

725
00:37:38,700 --> 00:37:40,340
So, is there anything we can do now

726
00:37:40,660 --> 00:37:42,100
to help repair your relationship?

727
00:37:43,460 --> 00:37:44,540
If I wanted to repair it,

728
00:37:44,580 --> 00:37:45,933
I wouldn't have said break up.

729
00:37:48,180 --> 00:37:48,940
What I mean is,

730
00:37:48,940 --> 00:37:50,740
we don't want your relationship issues

731
00:37:50,740 --> 00:37:52,866
to affect the company's
collaboration with He Han.

732
00:37:52,933 --> 00:37:54,155
He Han is a jerk,

733
00:37:54,820 --> 00:37:55,820
but to us,

734
00:37:56,020 --> 00:37:58,340
he is a useful jerk.

735
00:38:03,466 --> 00:38:04,955
Assign him a different editor.

736
00:38:06,977 --> 00:38:08,940
These are some
of the company's senior editors.

737
00:38:09,140 --> 00:38:10,140
They all really want

738
00:38:10,140 --> 00:38:11,340
to work with Mr. He Han.

739
00:38:12,060 --> 00:38:13,860
See if there's anyone
you'd like to meet.

740
00:38:14,020 --> 00:38:15,244
I can set it up right away.

741
00:38:18,620 --> 00:38:19,800
None of them is attractive.

742
00:38:21,540 --> 00:38:22,540
They're editors.

743
00:38:23,260 --> 00:38:25,380
Mr. He Han,
I'm helping you find a new editor.

744
00:38:25,580 --> 00:38:26,420
I know.

745
00:38:28,400 --> 00:38:29,740
Then, what are your requirements?

746
00:38:29,740 --> 00:38:31,044
I'll help you filter them.

747
00:38:33,020 --> 00:38:34,140
I only have two requirements.

748
00:38:34,220 --> 00:38:35,780
If you meet either one, it's fine.

749
00:38:35,955 --> 00:38:37,659
Either more attractive
than Lin Zhanqiao,

750
00:38:37,660 --> 00:38:38,940
or more famous than Lin Zhanqiao.

751
00:38:39,220 --> 00:38:39,980
If you could

752
00:38:39,980 --> 00:38:42,266
find someone more attractive
and more famous than her,

753
00:38:42,380 --> 00:38:43,140
that would be best.

754
00:38:43,940 --> 00:38:44,860
An attractive editor?

755
00:38:44,980 --> 00:38:46,100
Then you should come to me.

756
00:38:46,740 --> 00:38:47,820
That's easy to find.

757
00:38:49,180 --> 00:38:50,940
Finding another Lin Zhanqiao isn't easy.

758
00:38:51,420 --> 00:38:53,740
But finding a pretty girl?
That's easy, right?

759
00:38:56,620 --> 00:38:57,620
That's why some things

760
00:38:57,620 --> 00:38:59,444
really shouldn't be said carelessly.

761
00:38:59,860 --> 00:39:01,260
Just a couple of days ago, you said

762
00:39:02,580 --> 00:39:03,900
you two would never break up.

763
00:39:03,933 --> 00:39:05,860
And now you're acting
like strangers for life.

764
00:39:07,066 --> 00:39:08,420
That's quite a slap in the face.

765
00:39:09,660 --> 00:39:11,100
But I think it's the right thing.

766
00:39:11,740 --> 00:39:14,100
Writers and scholars,
carefree and romantic.

767
00:39:15,980 --> 00:39:17,900
I'm not here to drive
a wedge between you.

768
00:39:18,580 --> 00:39:19,460
Oh, come on, Mr. Fan.

769
00:39:19,460 --> 00:39:21,340
When have you ever
not come to stir things up?

770
00:39:24,460 --> 00:39:26,620
Since you're not
happy working with Chenxing,

771
00:39:26,900 --> 00:39:27,500
I'll buy

772
00:39:27,977 --> 00:39:29,020
Shattered Six States.

773
00:39:33,980 --> 00:39:35,540
Chenxing's people are still here.

774
00:39:39,140 --> 00:39:41,380
Price-wise,
I'll make Chenxing satisfied.

775
00:39:42,180 --> 00:39:42,740
Mr. Fan,

776
00:39:43,180 --> 00:39:45,100
you're trying
to take away our livelihood, huh?

777
00:39:46,020 --> 00:39:47,860
What livelihood?

778
00:39:48,500 --> 00:39:50,140
Isn't this just like ordering takeout?

779
00:39:50,940 --> 00:39:51,900
Whoever makes it better,

780
00:39:52,060 --> 00:39:53,020
you buy from them.

781
00:39:59,340 --> 00:39:59,780
No way.

782
00:40:00,355 --> 00:40:01,940
I will never sell Shattered Six States.

783
00:40:02,060 --> 00:40:03,355
We've all worked so hard on it.

784
00:40:03,460 --> 00:40:04,420
This isn't about money.

785
00:40:05,820 --> 00:40:06,420
Zhanqiao,

786
00:40:07,540 --> 00:40:08,620
this is your problem.

787
00:40:11,260 --> 00:40:12,860
Otherwise, you call He Han

788
00:40:13,340 --> 00:40:14,980
to apologize to him properly.

789
00:40:15,380 --> 00:40:16,620
If he forgives you,

790
00:40:17,100 --> 00:40:18,260
this whole thing goes away.

791
00:40:18,800 --> 00:40:19,820
I didn't do anything wrong.

792
00:40:19,820 --> 00:40:21,020
So, why should I apologize?

793
00:40:21,180 --> 00:40:22,140
Then, sell it to Mr. Fan.

794
00:40:22,700 --> 00:40:24,220
From a purely business perspective,

795
00:40:24,220 --> 00:40:26,111
this is indeed
a good deal for our company.

796
00:40:28,580 --> 00:40:29,220
I don't agree.

797
00:40:29,866 --> 00:40:31,266
You only have these two choices.

798
00:40:31,700 --> 00:40:32,380
Pick one.

799
00:40:40,580 --> 00:40:41,380
Pull up

800
00:40:41,488 --> 00:40:42,850
the data's readership numbers.

801
00:40:42,850 --> 00:40:44,820
You can sort them
from lowest to highest.

802
00:40:44,900 --> 00:40:45,977
It'll be easier to read.

803
00:40:46,044 --> 00:40:47,460
Take a look. Does this look better?

804
00:40:47,460 --> 00:40:48,333
Isn't it much better?

805
00:40:48,460 --> 00:40:49,780
Yes, thank you, Mr. Ling.

806
00:40:50,288 --> 00:40:51,460
And look at this red here...

807
00:40:51,460 --> 00:40:52,460
For something so simple,

808
00:40:52,488 --> 00:40:54,266
there's no need
to trouble Mr. Yikai, right?

809
00:40:54,300 --> 00:40:55,955
I'll have someone come teach you later.

810
00:40:56,380 --> 00:40:56,930
Thank you.

811
00:40:56,930 --> 00:40:58,460
Mr. Yikai, come to my office.

812
00:40:58,533 --> 00:41:00,111
If you don't understand,
just ask anytime.

813
00:41:00,180 --> 00:41:01,044
Thank you, Mr. Ling.

814
00:41:08,444 --> 00:41:09,866
What do you think about He Han?

815
00:41:10,260 --> 00:41:10,660
Sell it.

816
00:41:12,580 --> 00:41:14,620
Getting rid of a nuisance
and still making money,

817
00:41:14,980 --> 00:41:16,177
I'd be grateful for that.

818
00:41:17,620 --> 00:41:18,420
Then it's settled.

819
00:41:18,620 --> 00:41:20,660
As long as He Han agrees
to sell, we vote in favor,

820
00:41:20,866 --> 00:41:22,688
and Lin Zhanqiao's
objection won't matter.

821
00:41:23,900 --> 00:41:24,340
Agreed.

822
00:41:27,500 --> 00:41:28,955
But you really have no loyalty.

823
00:41:29,511 --> 00:41:31,180
You two were
at least college classmates,

824
00:41:31,180 --> 00:41:32,620
yet you'd rather stand with money

825
00:41:33,420 --> 00:41:34,620
than with your old classmate.

826
00:41:35,660 --> 00:41:37,340
Those two aren't even comparable.

827
00:41:37,466 --> 00:41:39,630
If it's a choice between the two,
who wouldn't pick money?

828
00:41:39,644 --> 00:41:40,888
And that's a lot of money.

829
00:41:43,644 --> 00:41:45,244
Let's have dinner together tonight?

830
00:41:46,380 --> 00:41:47,600
Bring your classmate along.

831
00:41:47,820 --> 00:41:48,860
Why always bring her

832
00:41:48,860 --> 00:41:50,180
when it's just us two eating?

833
00:41:51,260 --> 00:41:52,140
Because I'm afraid

834
00:41:52,355 --> 00:41:54,244
that it's just
the two of us having dinner.

835
00:41:56,100 --> 00:41:57,260
Have you heard this saying?

836
00:41:57,860 --> 00:41:58,900
The thing you fear the most

837
00:41:59,300 --> 00:42:00,540
is what you lack the most.

838
00:42:16,020 --> 00:42:17,020
What have you prepared?

839
00:42:17,860 --> 00:42:19,020
Just the basic materials.

840
00:42:21,100 --> 00:42:22,540
I kind of don't know what to say.

841
00:42:23,420 --> 00:42:24,500
Just keep the right mindset.

842
00:42:28,820 --> 00:42:29,180
Here.

843
00:42:54,940 --> 00:42:55,740
Mr. He Han.

844
00:43:05,090 --> 00:43:06,010
You know, sometimes fate

845
00:43:06,010 --> 00:43:07,690
just happens so suddenly.

846
00:43:09,680 --> 00:43:10,610
(Since we were kids,)

847
00:43:11,440 --> 00:43:13,360
(we've been learning in class)

848
00:43:14,440 --> 00:43:16,110
(how to make new friends.)

849
00:43:16,380 --> 00:43:17,950
The three of us
started this company together.

850
00:43:18,080 --> 00:43:19,950
We gave Zhanqiao
an equal share at the start

851
00:43:20,350 --> 00:43:21,640
because she had He Han.

852
00:43:21,640 --> 00:43:22,410
What do you want?

853
00:43:23,020 --> 00:43:24,250
Diluting her shareholding.

854
00:43:24,780 --> 00:43:26,250
What I'm considering

855
00:43:26,640 --> 00:43:27,290
is pushing her out.

856
00:43:29,040 --> 00:43:30,160
(I've been thinking.)

857
00:43:31,440 --> 00:43:34,720
(Everyone's most comfortable level of intimacy)

858
00:43:35,480 --> 00:43:42,810
(is probably different.)

859
00:43:43,810 --> 00:43:45,560
♪If the sky♪

860
00:43:46,070 --> 00:43:47,470
♪And the sea♪

861
00:43:48,010 --> 00:43:49,720
♪Turned upside down♪

862
00:43:51,280 --> 00:43:53,210
♪If a swimming fish♪

863
00:43:53,610 --> 00:43:57,000
♪Fell in love with a flying bird♪

864
00:43:58,770 --> 00:44:00,740
♪If back then♪

865
00:44:01,100 --> 00:44:05,510
♪We had never let go♪

866
00:44:06,110 --> 00:44:12,390
♪We wouldn't be lost in the crowd♪

867
00:44:13,510 --> 00:44:15,660
♪We met in a thirteenth month♪

868
00:44:15,660 --> 00:44:17,530
♪Held each other in a fifth season♪

869
00:44:17,710 --> 00:44:20,150
♪And found our way back whole♪

870
00:44:20,990 --> 00:44:23,160
♪So let this surging love♪

871
00:44:23,160 --> 00:44:27,590
♪Rise like tides that never fall♪

872
00:44:28,490 --> 00:44:30,670
♪If we're caught in a pouring rain♪

873
00:44:30,670 --> 00:44:31,760
♪That's alright♪

874
00:44:32,300 --> 00:44:33,050
♪If we're buried♪

875
00:44:33,050 --> 00:44:35,750
♪By passing years all the better♪

876
00:44:36,010 --> 00:44:38,190
♪At least we still can keep♪

877
00:44:38,370 --> 00:44:42,790
♪This one eternal photograph♪

878
00:44:58,550 --> 00:45:00,840
♪We're on misaligned tracks♪

879
00:45:00,840 --> 00:45:02,600
♪Running in opposite ways♪

880
00:45:02,720 --> 00:45:05,190
♪Searching all along the way♪

881
00:45:05,990 --> 00:45:08,150
♪For the fire of our younger hearts♪

882
00:45:08,340 --> 00:45:13,250
♪And the beauty lost in time♪

883
00:45:13,250 --> 00:45:16,770
♪This time don't lose each other again♪

884
00:45:17,010 --> 00:45:17,980
♪Only after loss♪

885
00:45:17,980 --> 00:45:20,610
♪Do we learn what truly matters most♪

886
00:45:21,020 --> 00:45:23,380
♪In another time and space♪

887
00:45:23,380 --> 00:45:24,940
♪We'll stay and walk together♪

888
00:45:24,940 --> 00:45:27,770
♪Till we grow old♪

889
00:45:28,730 --> 00:45:31,020
♪But still the sky will never♪

890
00:45:31,020 --> 00:45:33,690
♪Turn with the sea♪

891
00:45:36,210 --> 00:45:38,620
♪But still a swimming fish won't♪

892
00:45:38,620 --> 00:45:43,830
♪Fall in love with a flying bird♪
